				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The timing is as important as the operations you are performing. If you do some things too soon the PPU will screw up your scroll values, too late and you'll get a glitchy scanline. If you look at my code, I wrote some notes about the timing. You can do a lot of stuff ahead of time, at any point before the HBlank, and only the last couple of writes have to fall within HBlank. That's just 8 cycles in a a window of ~28 cycles, so it isn't so hard to get right.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
